    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Exclusive, legally secured rights determining who may publish, copy, or distribute a work of art, writing, music, photograph, or other work. Works protected by copyright require the permission of the creator or other rights holder for their use. Some nations have the provision of fair use, which allows for limited use for educational purposes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050615/IFLA Glossary for Art Librarians (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Derecho exclusivo, legalmente asegurado para reproducir (por escrito o impreso), publicar y vender el tema y la forma de una obra literaria, musical o artístico.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een exclusief, wettelijk beschermd recht waaronder men de inhoud en vorm van een literair, muzikaal of artistiek werk  kan namaken (door bijvoorbeeld te schrijven of drukken), publiceren en verkopen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>意指受到法律保護的獨有權利。著作權人能複製（以書寫或印刷的方式）、出版或販售文學、音樂或藝術作品的內容形式。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Direitos exclusivos legalmente garantidos que determinam quem pode publicar, copiar ou distribuir uma obra de arte, escrita, música, fotografia ou outra obra. Obras protegidas por direitos autorais requerem a permissão do criador ou de outro detentor de direitos para seu uso. Algumas nações oferecem o uso justo, o que permite o uso limitado para fins educacionais. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
